# CBA Terraform standards

Applies to `infra//` and platform infrastructure Terraform. **Agent loop never runs `terraform apply`.**

## Patterns (from infra/)

- **Modules:** prefer existing modules under `automation/terraform/` over inline resources.
- **Naming:** `azurerm_*` resources use consistent `primary` / `secondary` pairing when `var.secondary_region` is set.
- **Event Hub:** consumer groups named explicitly (e.g. `my-service-central` on `my-service-status` hub).
- **depends_on:** explicit when module outputs are required before child resources.
- **Tags:** follow workspace tagging conventions in parent module variables.

## Agent loop constraints

| Action | Allowed in loop |
|--------|-----------------|
| `terraform fmt` / `validate` | Yes (read-only validation) |
| `terraform plan` | Yes with human review of output |
| `terraform apply` | **No** — human gate only |
| Edit prod `*.tfvars` | **No** — denylist hook |

## Review checklist

- [ ] No secrets in `.tf` files (use Key Vault / variable refs)
- [ ] DR pattern respected when `secondary_region` non-empty
- [ ] knowledge-graph path from resource → consuming Java service documented in wiki if new
- [ ] DDog monitors updated in `DDog_1000896_iac_live` when observability surface changes

